"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[207],{207:function(e,t,a){a.r(t),a.d(t,{SEA_SERPENT:function(){return o}});let o={id:"seaSerpent",title:"The Sea Serpent Pirate",shortDescription:"Searching for a missing mother, the legendary Sea Serpent.",skillGrid:{exploration:["star","open","star","open","star","blocked","blocked"],brawn:["star","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],hunting:["star","open","open","blocked","star","blocked","blocked"],aim:["star","star","open","open","blocked","blocked","blocked"],swagger:["open","open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked"],navigation:["star","open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked"]},constellation:a(9774).R6,storyBlanks:[{number:1,prompt:"Something that smells very good",type:"text"},{number:2,prompt:"The pirate name of another player",type:"player_name"},{number:3,prompt:"A type of job",type:"text"},{number:4,prompt:"The sound an elephant makes",type:"text"},{number:5,prompt:"A large, dangerous predator",type:"text"}],backstory:"Ten years ago, my mother left our village to sail across the open seas. She said she'd return, and I always thought she would, but now she's been gone for an awfully long time. I don't know much about what happened, only that when she got on the ship, she'd said it smelled of {1}. She always was a sucker for {1}. I later learned that the ship was the personal vessel of an unnamed royal {3}, who legend says was actually a sea serpent in disguise, who was searching for new subjects to bring to their underwater kingdom.\n\nI've signed up with a pirate crew to cross the seas. So far I ain't seen a serpent, and instead of {1}, this here ship smells more like {2}. I don't really know nothin' about bein' a pirate, but hopefully it will lead me to information about my mother. I'm told that the sea serpent's call sounds like \"{4}!\" and I've been listenin' ever so carefully...",events:[{narrative:"There's a barnacle formation on the hull that forms a map of some sort, and I swear one of 'em looks like the island where my mother was born. However, these barnacles are more than just a clue; they're really tasty, and everyone seems to love 'em. I should scrape some more for the crew.",effect:"Supplies +3."},{narrative:"I saw it! The serpent! It rose for just a second, and was the most beautiful thing I'd ever seen! Its giant eye told me everythin' I needed to know. My mother is alive, and the serpent knows where she is!",effect:"Re-roll +2. Infamy +1."},{narrative:"The night was quiet, and the sea was calm. I thought I heard a familiar voice carried by the wind. It was my mum singin' me a lullaby. I can't be sure it wasn't just my imagination, but it gives me hope.",effect:"Crew +1. Discontent -2."},{narrative:"Under the moonlight, I saw the serpent again, and it dropped this odd treasure into the water for me. It was a brilliant, gleaming thing, and it reminds me of my mum. I'll keep it close to my heart.",effect:"Retrieve card 73 Serpent's Tear from the story deck."},{narrative:'The serpent was there again. This time, it looked right at me, and with its great, wise eyes, communicated to me without words. "Your mother is waiting," it said. "But you must prove yourself worthy of the deep kingdom." I swear, I will. For her.',effect:"Gain 1 skill of your choice. Infamy +2."}],endings:{bad:{threshold:"≤3",text:'Your pirate adventures come to an end without ever finding the sea serpent or your mother. You return to your village and try to resume a normal life, but the sea calls to you constantly. Every night you sit by the shore, listening for the "{4}" that would mean the serpent is near, but it never comes. Eventually, you marry a local {3} who smells a bit like {2}, which is to say not great. You name your first child after your mother, and tell her stories of the sea serpent every night. One night, the child goes missing. You find her at the shore, staring at the water. "I heard it, mama," she says. "The serpent called to me." You spend the rest of your life wondering.'},good:{threshold:"4",text:"After many months of searching, you finally find the serpent's underwater kingdom, accessible through a cave behind a waterfall on a remote island. There, in the depths, you find your mother. She is alive and well, living as an honored guest of the serpent monarch. She is overjoyed to see you. \"I always knew you'd come,\" she says, tears streaming down her face. She chose to stay, she explains, because the serpent's kingdom was the only place where she felt truly free. She smells of {1}, just like you remember. You spend several weeks with her before returning to the surface. You visit often, and live a fulfilling life knowing your mother is safe and happy, even if her home is at the bottom of the sea."},legendary:{threshold:"5",text:'The serpent rises from the depths one last time, and with a mighty "{4}!" it transforms before your eyes into its true form — a magnificent queen of the deep. With a gentle nudge of its great head, it guides you to an underwater palace of coral and pearl. There, sitting on a throne of shells, is your mother, the serpent\'s most trusted advisor. She looks at you with pride and says, "I always knew you had the heart of the sea in you." The serpent queen offers you a choice: stay in the underwater kingdom and rule alongside your mother, or return to the surface with the serpent\'s blessing. You choose to stay, and discover that you can breathe underwater, a gift passed down through your bloodline. You and your mother are reunited at last, rulers of a kingdom more beautiful than anything on the surface. The pirates above tell legends of the one who rode a {5} into the deep and never came back.'}}}}}]);